---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
THIS NOTICE APPLIES TO ALL WORKFLOWS CONTAINED IN THIS DIRECTORY
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```
Apache NiFi – Versioned Workflows Repository

This directory is intended for workflows versioned through Apache NiFi.
```

## WHY VERSION WORKFLOWS?

Versioning workflows in NiFi provides a safer and more organized way to
manage dataflows.

Main benefits include:

* Track workflow changes over time
* Maintain version history for rollback if necessary
* Improve collaboration between users and teams
* Increase workflow traceability and reproducibility
* Prevent accidental loss of validated configurations

## DIRECTORY PURPOSE

This directory is dedicated to storing workflows versioned directly from
Apache NiFi.

Only version-controlled workflows should be committed here.

## HOW TO VERSION A WORKFLOW

1. Right-click the Processor Group that contains the workflow you want
   to version.

2. Select one of the following options:

   Version -> Start Version Control

   or, for already versioned workflows:

   Commit Local Changes

3. In the "Save Flow Version" window:

   * In the "Bucket" field, select this directory.
   * Fill in the remaining fields as needed.
   * Save/commit the workflow version.

## NOTES

* Prefer committing validated and tested workflows only.
* Use meaningful commit messages whenever possible.
* Avoid versioning temporary or experimental flows unless necessary.
